  "text": "Predicative specifications can be combined using the familiar operators of boolean theory, along with all the usual program combinators (e.g., '.' is the sequencing combinator), as well as combinators for parallelism and communication through channels. Predicative programming also has a frame construct equivalent to that of [CITATION_1] . The specification frame w P means that predicate P can change variables w, but no other variables; if the state consists of variables w and , then frame w P is equivalent to",
